The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or machine learning (cs.LG). The use of LP-based frameworks and approximation algorithms further supports the possibility of belonging to these categories.
